\f2\b0\fs21 \cf16 \cb31 \strokec16 Orphie & Magus's CRIT Rate increases by 
\f0\b \cf32 \strokec32 25%
\f2\b0 \cf16 \strokec16 , and Aftershock DMG increases by 
\f0\b \cf32 \strokec32 85%
\f2\b0 \cf16 \strokec16 .\cb1 \
\cb31 Orphie & Magus initially gain 100 Bottled Heat, up to a maximum of 125.\cb1 \
\cb31 When Orphie & Magus are off-field, if Special Attack: Corrosive Flash is available and Energy is greater than or equal to 60, consume 30 Energy to automatically trigger EX Special Attack: Crimson Vortex instead.\cb1 \
\cb31 When the laser from EX Special Attack: Heat Charge hits enemies, all squad members gain Zeroed In for 12s. Repeated triggers reset the duration. Zeroed In increases Agent ATK by 
\f0\b \cf32 \strokec32 280
\f2\b0 \cf16 \strokec16 . When Orphie & Magus's initial Energy Regen is greater than or equal to 1.6, for every 0.1 initial Energy Regen above this threshold, ATK increases by an additional 20. The total increase from both initial and additional ATK increases cannot exceed 
\f0\b \cf32 \strokec32 700
\f2\b0 \cf16 \strokec16 . When an Agent with Zeroed In triggers Aftershock, their Zeroed In duration extends by 4s, up to a maximum extension of 20s.\cb1 \
\cb31 The fire blade attack from Basic Attack: High-Pressure Flamethrower, EX Special Attack: Watch Your Step, EX Special Attack: Crimson Vortex, EX Special Attack: Heat Charge, EX Special Attack: Fiery Eruption, Chain Attack: Overheated Barrel, and Ultimate: Dance With Fire all count as Aftershock DMG, and using these skills counts as triggering Aftershock.\cb1 \
